What’s a Program Event?
Program events like SCE's Save Power Days help lower demand during peak energy hours, like those hot summer afternoons when everyone's cranking up the air conditioning.
Smart thermostats help you use less energy during those peak hours (and earn more bill credits) by automatically cooling your home ahead of time.
You can expect up to 12 four-hour program events each year; these events take place from 2–6 p.m., and only on weekdays.
We'll credit your bill for $1.25 per kWh you save during program events; depending on the weather and your participation, you could earn up to $60 each year.
You can override your smart thermostat and there's no penalty for not participating in a program event, although you will earn fewer bill credits.
















Southern California Edison Co: Company Profile - Bloomberg



































































  









